Plastic bags in Kenya are causing a major environmental and health crisis, leading to a call for a ban by the United Nations Environment Programme.
Similar efforts are being made in Eritrea, San Francisco, and Los Angeles to reduce plastic bag usage.
Rwanda and Uganda have already taken steps to ban plastic bags due to their harmful impact on the environment.
Tanzania is also investing in a recycling plant to address the plastic waste issue.
The widespread use of plastic bags is causing significant pollution and health risks across Africa, prompting urgent action to protect the environment.
